processReviewIdSelectionWizardDialog

public static int processReviewIdSelectionWizardDialog(java.lang.String reviewPhaseNameKey,
                                                       org.eclipse.core.resources.IProject project,
                                                       boolean isMultipleChoiceEnabled)
Processes review id selection wizard. The default project would be based upon the selected project, which can be given FileResource.getSelectedProject(). After this wizard is finished, 1) review ID instance (determined by project name and review id) will be set to content provider model, 2) reviewer ID string was set to preference store.

Clients should not pass IProject to be null. If so, IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.

Parameters:
reviewPhaseNameKey - the review phase name key.
project - the project to be shown as a default in the dialog.
isMultipleChoiceEnabled - set true if the project choice is mulitpile. false if the project choice is only the passing project.
Returns:
the result code of the dialog. e.g WizardDialog.CANEL. See WizardDialog constants.
